{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I dabble in design. I'm a curator of architecture and design;"},{"time":3000,"text":"I happen to be at the Museum of Modern Art."},{"time":5000,"text":"But what we're going to talk about today"},{"time":8000,"text":"is really design. Really good designers are like sponges:"},{"time":11000,"text":"they really are curious"},{"time":13000,"text":"and absorb every kind of information that comes their way,"},{"time":17000,"text":"and transform it so that it can be used by people like us."},{"time":20000,"text":"And so that gives me an opportunity,"},{"time":22000,"text":"because every design show that I curate"},{"time":25000,"text":"kind of looks at a different world. And it's great,"},{"time":27000,"text":"because it seems like every time I change jobs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":31000,"text":"And what I'm going to do today is I'm going to give you a preview"},{"time":33000,"text":"of the next exhibition that I'm working on, which is called"},{"time":36000,"text":"\"Design and the Elastic Mind.\""},{"time":38000,"text":"The world that I decided to focus on this particular time"},{"time":42000,"text":"is the world of science and the world of technology."},{"time":45000,"text":"Technology always comes into play when design is involved,"},{"time":48000,"text":"but science does a little less."},{"time":50000,"text":"But designers are great at taking big revolutions that happen"},{"time":54000,"text":"and transforming them so that we can use them."},{"time":57000,"text":"And this is what this exhibition looks at."}]},{"cues":[{"time":61000,"text":"If you think about your life today,"},{"time":63000,"text":"you go every day through many different scales,"},{"time":66000,"text":"many different changes of rhythm and pace."},{"time":68000,"text":"You work over different time zones, you talk to very different people,"},{"time":72000,"text":"you multitask. We all know it, and we do it kind of automatically."},{"time":76000,"text":"Some of the minds in this audience are super elastic,"},{"time":79000,"text":"others are a little slower,"},{"time":81000,"text":"others have a few stretch marks, but nonetheless"},{"time":84000,"text":"this is a quite exceptional audience from that viewpoint."},{"time":88000,"text":"Other people are not as elastic."},{"time":90000,"text":"I can't get my father in Italy to work on the Internet."},{"time":93000,"text":"He doesn't want to put high-speed Internet at home."},{"time":95000,"text":"And that's because there's some little bit of fear,"},{"time":98000,"text":"little bit of resistance or just clogged mechanisms."},{"time":101000,"text":"So designers work on this particular malaise that we have,"},{"time":105000,"text":"these kinds of discomforts that we have,"},{"time":108000,"text":"and try to make life easier for us."},{"time":110000,"text":"Elasticity of mind is something that we really need, you know,"},{"time":114000,"text":"we really need, we really cherish and we really work on."},{"time":118000,"text":"And this exhibition is about the work of designers"},{"time":121000,"text":"that help us be more elastic,"},{"time":123000,"text":"and also of designers that really work on this elasticity"},{"time":127000,"text":"as an opportunity. And one last thing is that"},{"time":130000,"text":"it's not only designers, but it's also scientists."}]},{"cues":[{"time":132000,"text":"And before I launch into the display of some of the slides"},{"time":137000,"text":"and into the preview, I would like to point out"},{"time":139000,"text":"this beautiful detail about scientists and design."},{"time":143000,"text":"You can say that the relationship between science and design"},{"time":146000,"text":"goes back centuries. You can of course talk about"},{"time":148000,"text":"Leonardo da Vinci and many other Renaissance men and women --"},{"time":152000,"text":"and there's a gigantic history behind it."},{"time":155000,"text":"But according to a really great science historian you might know,"},{"time":159000,"text":"Peter Galison -- he teaches at Harvard --"},{"time":161000,"text":"what nanotechnology in particular and quantum physics"},{"time":165000,"text":"have brought to designers is this renewed interest,"},{"time":168000,"text":"this real passion for design."}]},{"cues":[{"time":171000,"text":"So basically, the idea of being able to build things bottom up,"},{"time":175000,"text":"atom by atom, has made them all into tinkerers."},{"time":178000,"text":"And all of a sudden scientists are seeking designers,"},{"time":181000,"text":"just like designers are seeking scientists."},{"time":184000,"text":"It's a brand-new love affair that we're trying to cultivate"},{"time":189000,"text":"at MOMA. Together with Adam Bly, who is the founder of Seed magazine --"},{"time":193000,"text":"that's now a multimedia company, you might know it --"},{"time":195000,"text":"we founded about a year ago a monthly salon"},{"time":200000,"text":"for designers and scientists, and it's quite beautiful."},{"time":202000,"text":"And Keith has come, and also Jonathan has come and many others."},{"time":205000,"text":"And it was great, because at the beginning was this apology fest --"},{"time":208000,"text":"you know, scientists would tell designers,"},{"time":210000,"text":"you know, I don't know what style is, I'm not really elegant."},{"time":213000,"text":"And designers would like, oh, I don't know how to do an equation,"},{"time":216000,"text":"I don't understand what you're saying. And then all of a sudden"},{"time":219000,"text":"they really started talking each others' language,"},{"time":221000,"text":"and now we're already at the point that they collaborate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":223000,"text":"Paul Steinhardt, a physicist from New York,"},{"time":226000,"text":"and Aranda/Lasch, architects, collaborated in an installation"},{"time":231000,"text":"in London at the Serpentine."},{"time":233000,"text":"And it's really interesting to see how this happens."},{"time":237000,"text":"The exhibition will talk about the work"},{"time":240000,"text":"of both designers and scientists,"},{"time":242000,"text":"and show how they're presenting the possibilities of the future to us."},{"time":246000,"text":"I'm showing to you"},{"time":247000,"text":"different sections of the show right now,"},{"time":249000,"text":"just to give you a taste of it."},{"time":250000,"text":"Nanophysics and nanotechnology, for instance,"},{"time":254000,"text":"have really opened the designer's mind."},{"time":256000,"text":"In this case I'm showing more the designers' work,"},{"time":258000,"text":"because they're the ones that have really been stimulated."},{"time":261000,"text":"A lot of the objects in the show are concepts,"},{"time":263000,"text":"not objects that exist already. But what you're looking at here"},{"time":268000,"text":"is the work of some scientists from UCLA."},{"time":271000,"text":"This kind of alphabet soup is a new way to mark proteins --"},{"time":274000,"text":"not only by color but literally by alphabet letters."},{"time":277000,"text":"So they construct it, and they can construct all kinds of forms"}]},{"cues":[{"time":280000,"text":"at the nanoscale. This is the work of design students"},{"time":283000,"text":"from the Royal College of Arts in London"},{"time":285000,"text":"that have been working together with their tutor, Tony Dunne,"},{"time":288000,"text":"and with a bunch of scientists around Great Britain"},{"time":291000,"text":"on the possibilities of nanotechnology for design in the future."},{"time":294000,"text":"New sensing elements on the body --"},{"time":296000,"text":"you can grow hairs on your nails,"},{"time":298000,"text":"and therefore grab some of the particles from another person."},{"time":301000,"text":"They seem very, very obsessed"},{"time":303000,"text":"with finding out more about the ideal mate."},{"time":305000,"text":"So they're working on enhancing everything: touch, smell --"},{"time":309000,"text":"everything they can, in order to find the perfect mate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":312000,"text":"Very interesting. This is a typeface designer"},{"time":315000,"text":"from Israel who has designed -- he calls them \"typosperma.\""},{"time":319000,"text":"He's thinking -- of course it's all a concept --"},{"time":322000,"text":"of injecting typefaces into spermatozoa,"},{"time":326000,"text":"I don't know how to say it in English -- spermatazoi --"},{"time":329000,"text":"in order to make them become -- to almost have a song"},{"time":333000,"text":"or a whole poem written with every ejaculation. (Laughter)"},{"time":340000,"text":"I tell you, designers are quite fantastic, you know."}]},{"cues":[{"time":342000,"text":"So, tissue design."},{"time":344000,"text":"In this case too, you have a mixture of scientists and designers."},{"time":348000,"text":"This here is part of the same lab at the Royal College of Arts."},{"time":352000,"text":"The RCA is really quite an amazing school from that viewpoint."},{"time":355000,"text":"One of the assignments for a year was to work with in-vitro meat."},{"time":358000,"text":"You know that already you can grow meat in vitro."},{"time":361000,"text":"In Australia they did it -- this research company, called SymbioticA."},{"time":364000,"text":"But the problem is that it's a really ugly patty."},{"time":368000,"text":"And so, the assignment to the students was,"},{"time":370000,"text":"how should the steak of tomorrow be?"},{"time":372000,"text":"When you don't have to kill cows and it can have any shape,"},{"time":375000,"text":"what should it be like?"},{"time":376000,"text":"So this particular student, James King,"},{"time":379000,"text":"went around the beautiful English countryside,"},{"time":381000,"text":"picked the best, best cow that he could see,"},{"time":384000,"text":"and then put her in the MRI machine."},{"time":386000,"text":"Then, he took the scans of the best organs and made the meat --"},{"time":390000,"text":"of course, this is done with a Japanese resins food maker,"},{"time":393000,"text":"but you know, in the future it could be made better --"},{"time":396000,"text":"which reproduces the best MRI scan of the best cow he could find."}]},{"cues":[{"time":400000,"text":"Instead, this element here is much more banal."},{"time":404000,"text":"Something that you know can be done already"},{"time":406000,"text":"is to grow bone tissue, so that you can make a wedding ring"},{"time":410000,"text":"out of the bone tissue of your loved one -- literally."},{"time":412000,"text":"So, this is indeed made of human bone tissue."}]},{"cues":[{"time":416000,"text":"This is SymbioticA, and they've been working --"},{"time":419000,"text":"they were the first ones to do this in-vitro meat --"},{"time":421000,"text":"and now they've also done an in-vitro coat, a leather coat."},{"time":424000,"text":"It's miniscule, but it's a real coat. It's shaped like one."},{"time":428000,"text":"So, we'll be able to really not have any excuse"},{"time":431000,"text":"to be wearing everything leather in the future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":434000,"text":"One of the most important topics of the show -- you know,"},{"time":437000,"text":"as anything in our life today,"},{"time":439000,"text":"we can look at it from many, many different viewpoints,"},{"time":441000,"text":"and at different levels."},{"time":442000,"text":"One of the most interesting and most important concepts"},{"time":445000,"text":"is the idea of scale. We change scale very often:"},{"time":448000,"text":"we change resolution of screens, and"},{"time":450000,"text":"we're not really fazed by it, we do it very comfortably."},{"time":454000,"text":"So you go, even in the exhibition,"},{"time":456000,"text":"from the idea of nanotechnology and the nanoscale"},{"time":458000,"text":"to the manipulation of really great amounts of data --"},{"time":461000,"text":"the mapping and tagging of the universe and of the world."},{"time":464000,"text":"In this particular case a section will be devoted"},{"time":467000,"text":"to information design."},{"time":468000,"text":"You see here the work of Ben Fry. This is \"Human vs. Chimps\" --"},{"time":472000,"text":"the few chromosomes that distinguish us from chimps."},{"time":475000,"text":"It was a beautiful visualization that he did for Seed magazine."},{"time":479000,"text":"And here's the whole code of Pac-Man, visualized"},{"time":482000,"text":"with all the go-to, go-back-to,"},{"time":484000,"text":"also made into a beautiful choreography."}]},{"cues":[{"time":487000,"text":"And then also graphs by scientists,"},{"time":489000,"text":"this beautiful diagraph of protein homology."},{"time":492000,"text":"Scientists are starting to also consider aesthetics."},{"time":494000,"text":"We were discussing with Keith Shrubb* this morning"},{"time":497000,"text":"the fact that many scientists"},{"time":499000,"text":"tend not to use anything beautiful in their presentations,"},{"time":502000,"text":"otherwise they're afraid of being considered dumb blondes."},{"time":505000,"text":"So they pick the worst background"},{"time":507000,"text":"from any kind of PowerPoint presentation, the worst typeface."},{"time":511000,"text":"It's only recently that this kind of marriage"},{"time":514000,"text":"between design and science is producing some of the first \"pretty\" --"},{"time":518000,"text":"if we can say so -- scientific presentations."},{"time":521000,"text":"Another aspect of contemporary design"},{"time":523000,"text":"that I think is mind-opening, promising"},{"time":526000,"text":"and will really be the future of design,"},{"time":527000,"text":"is the idea of collective design."},{"time":529000,"text":"You know, the whole XO laptop, from One Laptop per Child,"},{"time":533000,"text":"is based on the idea of collaboration and mash and networking."},{"time":537000,"text":"So, the more the merrier."},{"time":539000,"text":"The more computers, the stronger the signal,"},{"time":541000,"text":"and children work on the interface so that it's all based"},{"time":545000,"text":"on doing things together, tasks together."},{"time":548000,"text":"So the idea of collective design"},{"time":551000,"text":"is something that will become even bigger in the future,"},{"time":553000,"text":"and this is chosen as an example."}]},{"cues":[{"time":557000,"text":"Related to the idea of collective design and to the new balance"},{"time":560000,"text":"between the individual and the collectiveness, collectivity"},{"time":564000,"text":"is the idea of existence maximum."},{"time":566000,"text":"That's a term that I coined a few years ago"},{"time":568000,"text":"while I was thinking of how pressed we are together,"},{"time":571000,"text":"and at the same time how these small objects,"},{"time":575000,"text":"like the Walkman first and then the iPod,"},{"time":577000,"text":"create bubbles of space around us that enable us"},{"time":580000,"text":"to have a metaphysical space"},{"time":582000,"text":"that is much bigger than our physical space."},{"time":584000,"text":"You can be in the subway and you can be completely isolated"},{"time":588000,"text":"and have your own room in your iPod."}]},{"cues":[{"time":590000,"text":"And this is the work of several designers"},{"time":593000,"text":"that really enhance the idea of solitude and expansion"},{"time":597000,"text":"by means of various techniques."},{"time":599000,"text":"This is a spa telephone. The idea is that it's become so difficult"},{"time":603000,"text":"to have a private conversation anywhere"},{"time":604000,"text":"that you go to the spa, you have a massage, you have a facial,"},{"time":607000,"text":"maybe a rub, and then you have this beautiful pool"},{"time":609000,"text":"with this perfect temperature, and you can have"},{"time":611000,"text":"this isolation tank phone conversation"},{"time":614000,"text":"with whomever you've been wanting to talk with for a long time."},{"time":617000,"text":"And same thing here, Social Tele-presence."},{"time":620000,"text":"It's actually already used by the military a little bit,"},{"time":622000,"text":"but it's the idea of being able to be somewhere else"},{"time":625000,"text":"with your senses while you're removed from it physically."},{"time":629000,"text":"And this is called Blind Date. It's a [unclear],"},{"time":632000,"text":"so if you're too shy to be really at the date,"},{"time":634000,"text":"you can stay at a distance with your flowers"},{"time":636000,"text":"and somebody else reenacts the date for you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":639000,"text":"Rapid manufacturing is another big area"},{"time":642000,"text":"in which technology and design are, I think,"},{"time":646000,"text":"bound to change the world. You've heard about it before many times."},{"time":650000,"text":"Rapid manufacturing is a computer file"},{"time":652000,"text":"sent directly from the computer to the manufacturing machine."},{"time":655000,"text":"It used to be called rapid prototyping, rapid modeling."},{"time":659000,"text":"It started out in the '80s, but at the beginning"},{"time":661000,"text":"it was machines carving out of a foam block"},{"time":664000,"text":"a model that was very, very fragile,"},{"time":667000,"text":"and could not have any real use."},{"time":669000,"text":"Slowly but surely, the materials became better -- better resins."},{"time":673000,"text":"Techniques became better -- not only carving"},{"time":675000,"text":"but also stereolithography and laser -- solidifying all kinds of resins,"},{"time":681000,"text":"whether in powder or in liquid form. And the vats became bigger,"},{"time":685000,"text":"to the point that now we can have actual chairs"},{"time":688000,"text":"made by rapid manufacturing."},{"time":690000,"text":"It takes seven days today to manufacture a chair,"},{"time":693000,"text":"but you know what? One day it will take seven hours."},{"time":695000,"text":"And then the dream is that you'll be able to, from home,"},{"time":699000,"text":"customize your chair. You know, companies and designers"},{"time":701000,"text":"will be designing the matrix or the margins"},{"time":704000,"text":"that respect both solidity and brand, and design identity."},{"time":709000,"text":"And then you can send it to the Kinko's store at the corner"}]},{"cues":[{"time":712000,"text":"and go get your chair. Now, the implications of this are enormous,"},{"time":715000,"text":"not only regarding the participation of the final buyer"},{"time":719000,"text":"in the design process, but also no tracking,"},{"time":721000,"text":"no warehousing, no wasted materials."},{"time":724000,"text":"Also, I can imagine many design manufacturers"},{"time":727000,"text":"will have to retool their own business plans"},{"time":729000,"text":"and maybe invest in this Kinko's store. But it really is a big change."},{"time":733000,"text":"And here I'm showing a picture that was in Wired Magazine --"},{"time":736000,"text":"you know, the Artifacts of the Future section that I love so much --"},{"time":739000,"text":"that shows you can have your desktop 3D printer"},{"time":741000,"text":"and print your own basketball."},{"time":743000,"text":"But here instead are examples, you can already 3D-print textiles,"},{"time":747000,"text":"which is very interesting."},{"time":749000,"text":"This is just a really nice touch -- it's called slow prototyping."},{"time":752000,"text":"It's a designer that put 10,000 bees at work and they built this vase."},{"time":757000,"text":"They had a particular shape that they had to stay in."}]},{"cues":[{"time":760000,"text":"Mapping and tagging."},{"time":761000,"text":"As the capacity of computers becomes really, really big,"},{"time":765000,"text":"and the capacity of our mind not that much bigger,"},{"time":769000,"text":"we find that we need to tag as much as we can what we do"},{"time":772000,"text":"in order to then retrace our path."},{"time":775000,"text":"Also, we do it in order to share with other people."},{"time":777000,"text":"Again, this communal sense of experience"},{"time":780000,"text":"that seems to be so important today."},{"time":782000,"text":"So, various ways to map and tag"},{"time":785000,"text":"are also the work of many designers nowadays."},{"time":789000,"text":"Also, the senses -- designers and scientists all work on trying to expand"},{"time":793000,"text":"our senses capabilities so that we can achieve more."},{"time":797000,"text":"And also animal senses in a way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":800000,"text":"This particular object that many people love so much"},{"time":804000,"text":"is actually based on kind of a scientific experiment --"},{"time":807000,"text":"the fact that bees have a very strong olfactory sense,"},{"time":810000,"text":"and so -- much like dogs that can smell certain kinds of skin cancer --"},{"time":814000,"text":"bees can be trained by Pavlovian reflex"},{"time":818000,"text":"to detect one type of cancer, and also pregnancy."},{"time":821000,"text":"And so this student at the RCA"},{"time":823000,"text":"designed this beautiful blown-glass object"},{"time":826000,"text":"where the bees move from one chamber to the other"},{"time":829000,"text":"if they detect that particular smell"},{"time":831000,"text":"that signifies, in this case, pregnancy."},{"time":833000,"text":"Another shape is made for cancer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":835000,"text":"Design for Debate is a very interesting new endeavor"},{"time":839000,"text":"that designers have really shaped for themselves."},{"time":842000,"text":"Some designers don't design objects, products,"},{"time":845000,"text":"things that we're going to actually use,"},{"time":846000,"text":"but rather, they design scenarios that are object-based."},{"time":850000,"text":"They're still very useful."},{"time":852000,"text":"They help companies and other designers think better about the future."},{"time":856000,"text":"And usually they are accompanied by videos."},{"time":859000,"text":"This is quite beautiful. It's Dunne and Raby, \"All the Robots.\""},{"time":862000,"text":"Those are a series of robots that are meant to be taken care of."},{"time":866000,"text":"We always think that robots will take care of us,"},{"time":868000,"text":"and instead they designed these robots that are very, very needy."},{"time":870000,"text":"You need to take one in your arms and look at it in the eyes"},{"time":873000,"text":"for about five minutes before it does something."},{"time":875000,"text":"Another one gets really, really nervous if you get in to the room,"},{"time":878000,"text":"and starts shaking, so you have to calm it down."},{"time":880000,"text":"So it's really a way to make us think more"},{"time":883000,"text":"about what robots mean to us."},{"time":885000,"text":"Noam Toran and \"Accessories for Lonely Men\":"},{"time":889000,"text":"the idea is that when you lose your loved one"},{"time":891000,"text":"or you go through a bad breakup,"},{"time":893000,"text":"what you miss the most are those annoying things"},{"time":896000,"text":"that you used to hate when you were with the other person."},{"time":899000,"text":"So he designed all these series of accessories."},{"time":901000,"text":"This one is something that takes away the sheets from you at night."},{"time":906000,"text":"Then there's another one that breathes on your neck."},{"time":909000,"text":"There's another one that throws plates and breaks them."},{"time":911000,"text":"So it's just this idea of what we really miss in life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":915000,"text":"Elio Caccavale: he took the idea"},{"time":918000,"text":"of those dolls that explain leukemia."},{"time":921000,"text":"He's working on dolls that explain xenotransplantation,"},{"time":925000,"text":"and also the spider gene into the goat, from a few years ago."},{"time":930000,"text":"He's working for the exhibition on a whole series of dolls"},{"time":933000,"text":"that explain to children where babies come from today."},{"time":936000,"text":"Because it's not anymore Mom, Dad, the flowers and the bees,"},{"time":939000,"text":"and then there's the baby. No, it can be two moms, three dads,"},{"time":942000,"text":"in-vitro -- there's the whole idea"},{"time":945000,"text":"of how babies can be made today that has changed."},{"time":949000,"text":"So it's a series of dolls that he's working on right now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":953000,"text":"One of the most beautiful things"},{"time":954000,"text":"is that designers really work on life,"},{"time":957000,"text":"even though they take technology into account."},{"time":959000,"text":"And many designers have been working recently"},{"time":961000,"text":"on the idea of death and mourning,"},{"time":963000,"text":"and what we can do about it today with new technologies."},{"time":967000,"text":"Or how we should behave about it with new technologies."},{"time":970000,"text":"These three objects over there are hard drives"},{"time":973000,"text":"with a Bluetooth connection. But they're in reality"},{"time":976000,"text":"very, very beautiful sculpted artifacts"},{"time":979000,"text":"that contain the whole desktop and computer memory"},{"time":982000,"text":"of somebody who passed away."},{"time":984000,"text":"So instead of having only the pictures,"},{"time":986000,"text":"you will be able to put this object next to the computer"},{"time":989000,"text":"and all of a sudden have, you know,"},{"time":991000,"text":"Gertrude's whole life and all of her files"},{"time":994000,"text":"and her address book come alive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":995000,"text":"And this is even better. This is Auger-Loizeau, \"AfterLife.\""},{"time":998000,"text":"It's the idea that some people don't believe in an afterlife."},{"time":1001000,"text":"So to give them something tangible that shows that"},{"time":1004000,"text":"there is something after death, they take the gastric juices"},{"time":1008000,"text":"of people who passed away and concentrate them,"},{"time":1010000,"text":"and put them into a battery that can actually be used"},{"time":1013000,"text":"to power flashlights. They also go -- you know, sex toys, whatever."},{"time":1017000,"text":"It's quite amazing how these things can make you smile,"},{"time":1021000,"text":"can make you laugh, can make you cry sometimes."},{"time":1023000,"text":"But I'm hoping that this particular exhibition"},{"time":1026000,"text":"will be able to trace a new portrait of where design is going --"},{"time":1029000,"text":"which is always, hopefully, a portrait a few years in advance"},{"time":1032000,"text":"of where the world is going."},{"time":1034000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]}]}